				<p sameAs="title">Denunciation letter from Manuel Pereira to his uncle, a deputy of the Holy Office.</p>
				<p sameAs="summary">The author shares his suspicions about a man, Belchior Aranha, who had already been convicted for witchcraft. He was apparently practicing his 'arts' again.</p>
				<p sameAs="settingDesc"> The pharmacist Belchior Aranha, living in the region of Lamego, was accused by a priest of practicing witchcraft to cure the accuser's gout. He was convicted and sent to exile in Faro for two years.</p>
